.Dd April 20, 2026
.Dt OPERATOR.RS 7
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm operator.rs
.Nd Rust operator precedence and order of evaluation
.Sh DESCRIPTION
Operators are listed from highest to lowest precedence.
.Pp
.Bl -column "Operator                                    " "Associativity        " -offset indent -compact
.It Sy Operator Ta Sy Associativity Ta Sy Description
.It paths Ta Ta path expressions
.It "method()" Ta left to right Ta method calls
.It \&. Ta left to right Ta field access
.It "()  []" Ta left to right Ta call, index
.It \&? Ta Ta error propagation
.It "!  -  *  &  &mut" Ta Ta unary operators
.It as Ta left to right Ta type cast
.It \&*  /  % Ta left to right Ta arithmetic
.It \&+  - Ta left to right Ta arithmetic
.It \&<<  >> Ta left to right Ta bitwise shifts
.It \&& Ta left to right Ta bitwise AND
.It \&^ Ta left to right Ta bitwise XOR
.It \&| Ta left to right Ta bitwise OR
.It "==  !=  <  >  <=  >=" Ta require parentheses Ta comparison
.It \&&& Ta left to right Ta logical AND
.It \&|| Ta left to right Ta logical OR
.It "..  ..=" Ta require parentheses Ta range
.It "=  +=  -=  *=  /=  %=  &=  |=  ^=  <<=  >>=" Ta right to left Ta assignment
.It "return  break  closures" Ta Ta control flow
.El
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Lk https://doc.rust-lang.org/reference/expressions.html "The Rust Reference: Expressions"
.Sh HISTORY
Inspired by the
.Xr operator 7
man page, which documents C operator precedence and has shipped
with BSD since 4.3BSD in 1986.
